<section class="applications-section" id="coming-soon">
  <div class="inner">
    <h2 class="section-title">Coming Soon</h2>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col">
        <div class="card">
          <header>
            <h2>Climate</h2>
            <div class="icon"><svg class="icon"><use xlink:href="#shape-carbon"></use></svg></div>
          </header>
          <div class="content">
            <p>Track carbon emissions and removal from forest change</p>
          </div>
          <footer>
            <span class="btn soon">coming soon</span>
          </footer>
          <div class="description">
            <div class="additional-info">
              <h2>Climate</h2>
              <p>Global Forest Watch Climate is a new tool to track carbon emissions and removals from forest change. With GFW Climate, users will be able to visualize and analyze forest carbon data interactively and produce custom results and analytical content. GFW Climate provides a credible online tool that is timely, relevant and useful for stakeholders involved in designing forest policies that maximize potential for climate change mitigation.</p>            
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col">
        <div class="card">
          <header>
            <h2>Biodiversity</h2>
            <div class="icon"><svg class="icon"><use xlink:href="#shape-biodiversity"></use></svg></div>
          </header>
          <div class="content">
            <p>Monitor forest change in critical habitats and landscapes</p>
          </div>
          <footer>
            <span class="btn soon">coming soon</span>
          </footer>
          <div class="description">
            <div class="additional-info">
              <h2>Biodiversity</h2>
              <p>Global Forest Watch Biodiversity, an application under development through a partnership with <a target="_blank" href="http://www.resolv.org/">RESOLVE</a>, will unite the best available data for forests and biodiversity to monitor and manage critical habitats and species. With new biodiversity indicators, monitoring capabilities, and interactive dashboards, GFW Biodiversity will supply the information needed to assess and improve the current state of forest biodiversity and help countries reach international binding commitments.</p>            
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col">
        <div class="card">
          <header>
            <h2>Landsat Imagery Validation Application</h2>
            <div class="icon"><svg class="icon"><use xlink:href="#shape-landsat"></use></svg></div>
          </header>
          <div class="content">
            <p>Help make GFW forest alerts more reliable by identifying changes in Landsat imagery</p>
          </div>
          <footer>
            <span class="btn soon">coming soon</span>
          </footer>
          <div class="description">
            <div class="additional-info">
              <h2>Landsat Imagery Validation Application</h2>
              <p>Sometimes the human eye is more powerful than computer algorithms at spotting forest loss. This simple app displays recent satellite images of forest change alerts and asks users to classify what they see. User contributions help improve our alerting systems, flagging areas where data may be inaccurate. Become part of the GFW crowdsourcing community by identifying forest changes in satellite images.</p>            
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col">
        <div class="card">
          <header>
            <h2>GFW Mobile Data Application </h2>
            <div class="icon"><svg class="icon"><use xlink:href="#shape-globe-mobile"></use></svg></div>
          </header>
          <div class="content">
            <p>Access GFW forest change data and collect information from your mobile device</p>
          </div>
          <footer>
            <span class="btn soon">coming soon</span>
          </footer>
          <div class="description">
            <div class="additional-info">
              <h2>GFW Mobile Data Application </h2>
              <p>This easy-to-use app enables local stakeholders with limited or occasional internet connectivity to use and contribute data to the GFW platform using mobile and cloud technologies. With this app, users can find forest clearing alerts on the ground in their area of interest and collect and report information from the field. Global Forest Watch is currently developing this tool with Google and the Jane Goodall Institute.</p>            
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
